		<title>How stablecoins became part of Nigeria&#8217;s central bank&#8217;s plan for payments </title>
		<link>https://techcabal.com/2026/06/15/how-stablecoins-became-part-of-nigerias-central-banks-plan-for-payments/</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Temitayo Jaiyeola]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Mon, 15 Jun 2026 08:21:40 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[Follow the Money]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[CBN]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Nigeria]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[stablecoins]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://techcabal.com/?p=190121</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[The Central Bank of Nigeria (CBN) mentioned stablecoin(s) at least 68 times in its newly released Payments System Vision 2028 (PSV 2028).  For a regulator that once wanted banks nowhere near cryptocurrency businesses, this is a remarkable shift. ]]></description>
